textView.mutableString: This software is provided as is by the University of Malta with the support of RIDT Funding. The developers make no guarantees about the accuracy of the said software, and are not liable to any damages due to information inaccuracy. The Aim of the application is solely to collect data about journeys carried out by typical users throughout the day for the purpose of Academic research only. Use of the App is restricted to persons who are 18 years or older, and is completely voluntary.

In order to carry out our research we ask you the user for generic personal information which is typically associated with Transport Surveying. These are your Gender, Age Group, Relationship to the University of Malta and whether you have access to a personal vehicle. This data is used in accordance with the University's Data Protection Guidelines. Once provided this information is tied with your Journay data in our database only through a unique identifier, which identifier is similarly anonymous. The application allows you to reset your unique identifier by resetting the application data and requesting a new one. The application also gives you complete control over when to start and stop the loggince process and over which journeys are uploaded to our servers.

fragment.string: The Main Control Screen (which can be accessed by pressing on the Main Tab) provides you with the ability to start/stop the tracking service. The

button is used to start the tracking process. You do not need to physically start tracking before each journey: rather the algorithm is intelligent enough to automatically turn on or off the GPS and partition your trips on its own, as long as the process is active. You may need to occasionally stop tracking for privacy or battery-related reasons. In this case, press the

fragment.content: Button which will terminate the online process and generate a list of journeys for you to selectively upload.

fragment.string: Selecting the Journeys Tab brings up the Journey List Screen, from where you can view the list of tracked journeys so far and upload them at your discretion to our server for processing. Clicking on any Journey brings up the

fragment.content: Screen. This allows you to view the journey path traversed and set the

fragment.string: for the changes to be registered. From the Journey List, you can choose to delete certain journeys or upload them to our server. If you decide to upload journeys make sure you are connected to the internet, preferably over a non-metered connection as otherwise you can incur charges. Uploaded Journeys will be deleted from your local cache.
